Salvador Dali saw all Lenin, Hitler, Franco, etc. as the "great masturbators" over the world. Pharaoh gooning into the Nile. Houdini also seems to embody this type of man. His relationship with H. Lovecraft also hints at an unrealized (?) potential "elite" status, like Roosevelt.

Often times when one is forced to do unproductive labor he will try to rationalize it to himself. Like a college student going to classes he knows he can easily pass without attending, reading the superfluous textbooks diligently to pretend his/her education is important or real.

Dr. Hans Selye showed unproductive labor is one of the worst, most stressful things possible. Not coincidence that being forced to e.g. clean the toilets with a toothbrush, measure the floors with a toothpick, etc. is used in many militaries to break the spirit of new soldiers.
